                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/433: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-30T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1926—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 31—2:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>521. My 520, October 30, 2 p.m., paragraph 1.</p>
                <p>[1.] Following from American consul general, Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 30, 1 p.m. Your October 29, 11 a.m.<note n="77"
                                xml:id="d688fn77">See telegram No. 520 bis., Oct. 30, from the
                                Chargé, <ref target="#pg_893">p. 893</ref>.</note> I have concurred
                            in the protest against the inspection regulations which the senior
                            [apparent omission] will now hand to Chen.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>2. Jenkins resumed charge on the 30th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
